    "body": "> @benjthayer WDYT about using wallets with empty names?\r\n> \r\n> In the linked PR 2 options have been proposed:\r\n> \r\n> 1. Do not allow empty wallet name by validating the wallet name edit field\r\n> 2. Display some placeholder text in the Minting wallet accounts dropdown when the name is empty.\r\n> \r\n> These 2 options could work well together to fix current accounts with empty wallet names and also prevent empty wallet names from now on.\r\n\r\nHi @alexjba I would think route 1 would be best - validating against an empty name both at the point of account creation and when editing the name- this will avoid missing wallet names altogether. \r\n\r\nWhile it's nice to give the user as much creative freedom as possible, there is little utility in an empty name and allowing them to do this would lead to a few UX issues later down the line as you rightly pointed out. \r\n\r\nIf the user doesn't want to name their account, they can always stick with the automatically generated name `Account [number of account]` that is populated into the name field when the user is creating the account.\r\n\r\nhttps://www.figma.com/file/FkFClTCYKf83RJWoifWgoX/Wallet-v2?type=design&node-id=15742-499323&t=kvNFpKtgHWy8Twvp-4\r\n\r\ncc @John-44 ",
